Consul Restaurant Corp said itextended the deadline of its exchange offer for its 13 pctconvertible debentures due 1992 to 1700 CDT April 24.    The offer originally was scheduled to expire April 13.    It said investor response to the offer has been favorable,but a higher exchange level is needed if the company is to meetits 90 pct acceptance level. On March 16 Consul offered toexchange each 1,000 dlr face value of bonds for 10 shares ofpreferred stock, convertible after Dec 1, 1987 into a total of500 shares of common stock. In addition, tendering andnon-tendering investors will receive the bonds' May Oneinterest payment in common stock. Reuter&#3;